                  <msItem xml:id="WadhMinasian_425-item3" n="3">
                     <locus from="129b" to="133a">ff. 129b-133a</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note type="content-genre">History</note>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2978">Tarjumah va sharḥ-i ʾAsrār al-Shahādah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_2978">ترجمه و شرح اسرار الشهاده</title>
                     <author key="person_64932206" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/64932206">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Rashtī, Kāẓim ibn Qāsim, -1843</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">رشتی، کاظم بن قاسم، -۱۸۴۳</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Rashtī, Sayid Kāẓim ibn Qāsim (1259 Qamarī/1843)</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">رشتی، سید کاظم بن قاسم (۱۲۵۹ق/۱۸۴۳م)‏</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note xml:lang="en">ʾAsrār al-shahādah is one of the works by Sayid Kāẓim Rashtī. Once on his return journey from Karbalā, while stopping in Qazvīn due to an illness, the author asked the translator - who was one of his followers - to translate this book into Persian. Upon a request from ʿAbd al-Vahhāb Qazvīnī, the book of Asrār al-shahādah sets out to describe and analyze the martyrdom of Ḥaz̤rat-i Imām Ḥusayn (sa) and the secrets of the Ṭaf event (Karbalā). It also includes some related hadiths and a comparative statement about some Quranic verses and the incidents of Āshūrā.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسمله، حمد و ثنایی که فوایح روایح اخلاص و اختصاصش فیض اثمار جنت الماوی و طیب…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">… و بقدر مقدور بایضاح تعبیر معانی کوشیده تا مقصود آن مقصد. و صلی الله علیهم… اعوذ بالله من الشیطان الرجیم.</explicit>
                     <colophon>None.</colophon>
                     <listBibl>
                        <head>Sequence Number in the Persian Catalogue:</head><bibl>FAW 182</bibl>
