                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="WadhMinasian_425-item4" n="4">
                     <locus from="133a" to="161a">ff. 133a-161a</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2979">Dalīl al-mutaḥayyirīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_2979">دلیل‌المتحیرین</title>
                     <author key="person_64932206" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/64932206">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Rashtī, Kāẓim ibn Qāsim, -1843</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">رشتی، کاظم بن قاسم، -۱۸۴۳</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Rashtī, Sayid Kāẓim ibn Qāsim (1259 Qamarī/1843)</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">رشتی، سید کاظم بن قاسم (۱۲۵۹ق/۱۸۴۳م)‏</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note xml:lang="en">Sayid Kāẓim Rashtī, who was the second in rank after Shaykh Aḥmad Iḥsāʾī of Shaykhiyah, was questioned by a number of Shaykhiyah believers about their beliefs. He therefore authored this book in Arabic detailing their beliefs, as well as giving a biography of Shaykh Aḥmad Iḥsāʾī, the founder of Shaykhiyah faith, including his written works and permissions. The current copy is a Persian translation of the book by one of the author's followers, Muḥammad Raz̤ī bin Muḥammad Riz̤ā. It has been printed several times.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسمله، حمدله، اما بعد چنین گوید بنده جانی و اسیر فانی کاظم ابن قاسم الحسینی الرشیدی که جناب مولای امجد و بزرگوار…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">… فی کربلا الحسین ع علیه و صلوات الله و سلامه شرف الله بشرف الاصول فانه غایة المامول و نهایة المسول. بتاریخ شب یازدهم شهر شوال المعظم تمام شد سنه ۱۲۵۸.</explicit>
